qx|1.,wide|ht|b|CS|1|CP|4|fp|1|at|^-{      Problems      }
^-|CS||CP||fp||ht|d|at|^B@24NT ace asking and the Roman Keycards conventions ignore the Useful Space Principle (USP) |CP|1|AT|^*H//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Useful_space_principle^*N|CP||AT| because bidding spaces are not allocated where most needed. At times using one of those conventions can throw partnership into an unmakable contract. For example if the agreed trump suit is clubs and 5@D is the response after 4NT call (0314 Blackwood ), partnership probably could be forced to play a doomed 6@C contract.|
