ht|k|CS|1|CP|4|fp|1|at|^-{Concept
          Useful Space Principle          }
^-|CS||CP||fp||ht|m|va|4|CS||CP||fp||at|^B@2
Useful Space Principle (USP) tells bidding theorists that bidding space should be allocated where it is most needed. Mr. Jeff Rubens conceived the Useful Space Principle which in a series of articles published in The Bridge World, from November 1980 through April 1981. Patterning along the USP he also designed Kickback Convention. It is to remedy the problems associated with regular Blackwood and Roman Keycard Conventions. Of course with a price which the proponent claim being negligible and manageable. |
